Part A: Subjects, Objects, and Rules
*What is a subject in access control? A person or system trying to access something.
*What is a object? Its the thing the subject wants to access.
*What are rules? What i am allowed to do.
*Give a real-life example (like school lockers, libary books, or computer logins). School lockers.
*Why do these accounts need stronger protection? So people can't access it easily.
*Give one example of a privileged account in real life and what they say have access to that other people wouldn't. System Administrators has full access over IT infrastructure.
*Why do these accounts need stronger protection? So it would be harder for intruders to access accounts.
